r that directly, which makes this a concrete and important omission.\n\nLet me verify I haven't missed any other inaccuracies by spot-checking the source material against what's documented. The narrow/compact mode slide menu behavior is verbatim from the source, and the html_head.jsp reference checks out. I think I've identified the main issues now.\n\nLooking at my findings, the critical problem is that V1 completely omits the default CSS color variable values—the RGB definitions for baseColor, mainColor1, mainColor2, and subColor. V4 has a related minor issue where it's missing those property names in the table. There's also a minor point about V1 leaving out the \"increased support cost\" context for IE6/7 support, though the technical constraints are more directly relevant to the decision. I'm confirming the document's scope covers both modification procedures and their impact/cost implications, which aligns with my three key findings about the CSS color defaults, missing property hints, and IE6/7 cost warnings.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":21544,"cache_read_input_tokens":18400,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":21544,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4078a9e5-ac32-4ace-a85d-fb78e3bce2fd","uuid":"86591bf9-f5d4-45aa-b083-893c8092ba6c"}
